OL,3,C'Being alone without support is the
OL,4,Cworst': Life as a homeless teenager
OL,6,FElliot has also received support from
OL,7,FGorwel. He says nothing could've
OL,8,Fprepared him for homelessness.
OL,10,FHe said: "I had no support whatsoever,
OL,11,Fand you're just left on your own and
OL,12,Fyou just have to wait."
OL,14,FHe believes the government's plans
OL,15,Fneed to prevent more people from
OL,16,Ffalling into homelessness. He said:
OL,17,F"It's going to be difficult. I think
OL,18,Feveryone just needs to look out for
OL,19,Fthe signs of what could happen."
