OL,6,FThe Homelessness and Social Housing
OL,7,FAllocation (Wales) Bill will need to
OL,8,Fbe voted through by Senedd members
OL,9,Fbefore it comes into law, and
OL,10,Ftherefore may be amended. Some of the
OL,11,Fkey points currently include:
OL,13,FThe Cabinet Secretary for Housing and
OL,14,FLocal Government, Jayne Bryant,
OL,15,Fdescribed the Bill as a "turning
OL,16,Fpoint" in how Wales approaches
OL,17,Fhomelessness and said the legislation
OL,18,Fwill help "transform lives".
